Rating: 3
I thought this were very good, but I wonder if they might be even better with some type of dipping sauce. I did not toast the tortillas prior to stacking them, and I grilled the slices in a frying pan. I cut them into bite size pieces (held with toothpicks) and served as hors d' oeuvres at a cocktail party. I liked that the combination of sweet and savory going on, but I think they could've used just a little something else, like a dipping sauce. Maybe something with a bit of spice to it. So, if you have any ideas, please post....

