Rating: 3
This is an awesome side dish to accompany grilled meats. I've made it several times and guests have loved it. The tortillas tend to melt in with the onion mix and the end result is quite creamy and simply superb. Guests don't even realize it's made out of tortillas. I would always do this on the grill and agree with previous counsel to make extra onion mix. The existing recipe gives one barely enough onion mixture to complete a sufficient number of layers. Great with the grilled rib-eyes with bernaise butter.

